<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro digest_ext_error(da) expands to the constant expression (false). When that macro is used as a controlling expression (for example: if (digest_ext_error(&da)) ret = MHD_NO; in MHD_digest_auth_calc_userhash) the controlling expression is invariant (always false). This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3 because the controlling expression is constant and not one of the permitted exceptions (not an infinite loop or the allowed do-while false case).
</scenario>
